Class Capabilities

All Implemented Interfaces:

Direct Known Subclasses:
LayerCapabilities, ServiceCapabilities
public class Capabilities
extends Object
implements Cloneable

The Capabilities class defines a collection of capabilities. Any code can add new capabilities, however, capability names must be unique. If you attempt to add a capability with the same name as an existing capability, then you'll get a negative return value from the add() method and the operation will not succeed. Only sub-classes may modify the availability of an existing capability.

NOTE: This class operates on unsychronized collection classes, and does not manage additional synchronization. It is anticipated that the majority of uses of this class will not need synchronization, but if you're concerned, you need to manage this yourself in calling code.

addCapability

public int addCapability(Capability capability)
Adds a capability to the collection and return the index where it can be found in the the collection. Alternatively, if a Capability with that name already exists within the collection then -1 is returned and nothing new is added to the collection.

Parameters:
capability - the capability
Returns:
the index of the capability within the collection, or -1 == a capability with the name already exists
Throws:
IllegalArgumentException - if capability is null
